column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear  No Precipitation  Heavy Wind
column13: Control looks clear. Flow through medium sized shrubs/brush. Bottom is sility and uneven from cows crossing.
column14: Wading mmnt below cable way 10m beow gauge. Close to max wade max depth was 1.03m could have done a bit more. Velocitys not a factor in difficulty. Dead flow on banks.  Moderate SRC found to HG purged then reset to found WL from DWL. Took ECG reading and it agreed with DWL reset amasser to ECG reading. Well is connected no ice in well. Flushed intakes.  Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Mostly Cloudy  No Precipitation  Moderate Wind
column13: Caved in hanging ice at control. Anchor ice on bottom on channel.
column14: Good chop and wade 15m DS. Dead flow and wierd angles on right bank but overall good. Large SRC found to HG reset to found WL.Float was found pinned far above ice in well went to lower  float then beads slipped. Set Float on top of ice and took an ECG to the top of the ice. Set Amasser to ECG reading then pinned just above ice at 11:15. Expect an SRC to the amasser come open water. HG2 invalid. Did before and after WL as measurement caused some BW stage tracking well before departure. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Vegetation; Cloudy  Mist  Moderate Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13: A lot of tall grass and willows in the channel makes it difficult for the ADCP to perform a profile. This channel shoul be cleared with a brush cutter at the ADCP measurement area.
column14: ***REVISED MMNT. REMOVED TRANSECT 4 SINCE IT LOST BOTTOM TRACK AND GAINED 4m EXTRA WIDTH. REMOVED 005 TO RETAIN RECIP PAIRS. ADJUSTED BOTTOM EXTRAP TO ACCOUNT FOR HEAVY VEG ALONG CHANNEL BED. TEXT FILE WITH MORE RATIONALE SAVED IN MEASUREMENT FOLDER AND APPENDED TO FV - LKR 20231130****  I have no thermometer to check the water temperature I guessed at the 5 degrees for the ADCP configuration . Wrong date (April 19) used for ADCP configuration. Today is April 20. Difficulty seeing and operating the touch screen of the tablet in this moist cool windy weather. Extremely difficult to control the ADCP because of the helical velocities created by the heavy brush and grass in the channel. I did 14 transects and the StreamPro ADCP managed to consistently average 6.4 cms. Best I could accomplish in the conditions of this channel. A lot of "blanking" data because of tracking issues. The ability to do a conventional measurement from the cabeway has been taken away; so this is the best results of a flow measurement possible. @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller 2016) 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @  Thin ice in the well; float stuck to the ice but value was close to the ECG reading. Because of the thaw I had to walk in to this site. Approximately 2.5 km one way. The FTS logger display would not light up. I texted Matt through the Garmin Satellite device to confirm that the data was transmitting. Logger needs to be replaced. No download. The only HG's available were from the FTS Bubbler display. HG minus the "offset" of .051 indicates a sensor depth of 2.961 at 09:16   No download because the logger has no display. ADCP by Moving Boat
